  description="A qubit is a two-level quantum system whose state is α|0⟩+β|1⟩ with |α|²+|β|²=1. This page covers the definition, the Bloch sphere as the geometric representation of pure single-qubit states, the photonic encodings used to carry qubits across a network, the matter encodings used to store and process them, and DiVincenzo's criteria."
